cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.SI 

The paper deals with classification and regression fusion models for remote sensing applications, which are typically related to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed models also involve dealing with ambiguously and imprecisely labeled training data, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the use of multiple-instance learning framework is relevant to the sub-category of signal processing (cs.SI).
